{
  "doc_id": "prion_0544",
  "text": "We report a 26-year-old woman with Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD) who had received cadaveric dural material 33 months before the onset of neurologic symptoms.\nThis is the fourth case in which a dural graft was the putative source of the CJD agent.\nAll four cases had the grafting before changes in the sterilization procedure adopted in 1987 to inactivate the CJD agent.",
